    "body": "@acolytec3 I'm glad you're updating the *token registry*, but this issue is about something else.\r\n\r\nYou can select the value of your wallet to be displayed in fiat currencies (USD, INR, etc.). What I want is to have Dai among these currencies. So when I have 1 ETH and 100 Dai, it will read something like \"225 DAI\" (not exactly, because both  ETHUSD *and* DAIUSD can change). And the value of each stored volatile asset, and transaction fee equivalents, and anything for which the wallet currency is used, would be displayed in Dai as well.\r\n\r\n**Tl;dr**: let's be able to have no dirty stinkin fiat on the screen and get us used to accounting in Dai.",
